# ============================================================================
# ShopShadow Backend - Environment Configuration
# ============================================================================
# This file contains environment variable templates for ShopShadow backend
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in the values for your environment
# 3. Never commit .env to version control (it contains secrets)
#
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# DATABASE CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================

# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (PostgreSQL)
# By default, use local PostgreSQL for development:
#
# Prerequisites:
# 1. Install PostgreSQL: https://www.postgresql.org/download/
# 2. Create database: createdb shopshadow
# 3. Set DATABASE_URL below with your local credentials
#
# Example for macOS/Linux (default PostgreSQL user):
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/shopshadow

# Example for Windows (PostgreSQL installer):
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/shopshadow

# ============================================================================
# SUPABASE (Production/Cloud - Future Migration)
# ============================================================================
#
# When migrating to Supabase:
# 1. Create a new Supabase project at https://supabase.com
# 2. Go to Project Settings â†’ Database
# 3. Copy the connection string (select "URI" tab)
# 4. Replace the DATABASE_URL below
#
# Supabase Example:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@db.[PROJECT-REF].supabase.co:5432/postgres
#
# Benefits of Supabase:
# - Managed PostgreSQL database
# - Built-in authentication (optional)
# - Cloud storage for files (basket photos, receipts)
# - Row-level security (RLS) for data access control
# - Auto-scaling and backups
#

# ============================================================================
# MIGRATION SETUP
# ============================================================================
#
# The migration system uses the DATABASE_URL environment variable.
#
# Common Commands:
# - npm run migrate:up       # Apply pending migrations
# - npm run migrate:down     # Rollback last migration
# - npm run migrate:create   # Create new migration file
#
# The pgmigrations table tracks applied migrations automatically.
#

# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# - Change 'password' to your actual PostgreSQL password
# - For local development, ensure PostgreSQL service is running
# - The database 'shopshadow' must exist before running migrations
# - Check migrations/ directory for all applied migrations
#
